<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.504/2310a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-28">May 28, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>867. Justice has telegraphed the following instruction district directors
                            of immigration, “Effective immediately, nationals of Mexico are not to
                            be admitted as agricultural workers under the provisions of Public Law
                            45 and Regulations 8C4115 unless they present written consent of the
                            Federal Government of Mexico to emigrate for that purpose.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
